From: tawc
Origin: own

Expose `kumquat::KumquatBuilder` and friends as a library so the
compositor can run kumquat in-process on a dedicated thread instead
of spawning the upstream `kumquat` binary as a separate Android
process. Same code, different entry point.

Why in-process: kumquat's SCM_RIGHTS fd-passing requires the server
and the chroot client to share an SELinux domain (see
notes/gfxstream-bridge.md "Why kumquat must run as untrusted_app").
Running kumquat as a thread of the compositor app collapses that
constraint trivially — same uid, same context — and removes the
broker daemon spawn / pidfile / lifecycle plumbing.

The added `lib.rs` is a 2-line re-export. `main.rs` keeps building
unchanged: cargo allows a single crate to ship both `[[bin]]` and
`[lib]`, and the bin still references `kumquat::KumquatBuilder`
through its own `mod kumquat;` decl.

diff --git a/kumquat/server/Cargo.toml b/kumquat/server/Cargo.toml
--- a/kumquat/server/Cargo.toml
+++ b/kumquat/server/Cargo.toml
@@ -8,6 +8,10 @@ description = "A Rust server designed for virtio-multimedia use cases"
 repository = "https://github.com/magma-gpu/rutabaga_gfx"
 rust-version = "1.81.0"

+[lib]
+name = "kumquat_virtio"
+path = "src/lib.rs"
+
 [[bin]]
 name = "kumquat"
 path = "src/main.rs"
diff --git a/kumquat/server/src/lib.rs b/kumquat/server/src/lib.rs
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/kumquat/server/src/lib.rs
@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@
+// tawc-fork: lib target for the kumquat server modules so embedders
+// (the tawc compositor) can spin up `KumquatBuilder` on a thread
+// instead of forking the upstream `kumquat` binary.
+
+pub mod kumquat;
+pub mod kumquat_gpu;
